<!-- 8. & 9. FOUNDER & PHILOSOPHY SECTIONS -->
<section id="founder" class="py-5 section-darker">
  <div class="container py-5 reveal">
    <div class="row gx-5 align-items-center">
      <div class="col-lg-5 mb-5 mb-lg-0 text-center">
        <!-- Founder Portrait Placeholder -->
        <div class="founder-portrait founder-portrait-frame mx-auto rounded-4 shadow-glow-accent overflow-hidden position-relative mb-4">
           <i class="bi bi-person-fill founder-icon-xl text-white position-absolute top-50 start-50 translate-middle"></i>
        </div>
        <h3 class="fw-bold text-primary-color mb-1">Sabith Ali</h3>
        <p class="text-secondary-color fs-5">Founder & CEO, BeYa</p>
      </div>
      <div class="col-lg-7">
        <h6 class="text-uppercase text-secondary-color fw-bold mb-3 text-tracking-2">Our Philosophy</h6>
        <h2 class="fw-bold section-title mb-4">The Most Powerful Change Agent Is <span class="gradient-text-2">Already Inside the System.</span></h2>

        <div class="founder-narrative">
          <p class="text-secondary-color fs-5 mb-4 text-lh-17">
            For 13 years, Sabith Ali trained over 100,000 individuals across schools, corporates, and hospitals. But the core question remained: <strong>“What will people do differently tomorrow?”</strong>
          </p>
          <p class="text-secondary-color fs-5 mb-4 text-lh-17">
            His leadership philosophy rejects motivation as a long-term solution. Instead of external interventions that fade when the trainer leaves, BeYa builds internal systems, multiplies insider trainers, and empowers existing people to manage themselves with constitutional dignity.
          </p>

          <blockquote class="blockquote border-start border-4 border-glow ps-4 mt-4 py-2">
             <p class="text-primary-color fs-4 fst-italic fw-medium mb-0">"Dignity is not given — it is built through small, consistent daily actions."</p>
          </blockquote>
